args:
A false lord wielding the power of someone strong.
Not only do you hold your position unjustly,
you are a fiend whose misrule has brought great
suffering upon your people. I can no longer
overlook you wielding such misbegotten gains.
So tonight, I'm coming to take the source\nof that tenuous power—your contract.\n—The Phantom Thief Mona
What in the heavens?! Phantom Thief?!\nPress my frock, this MUST be a jape!
But what is this bit about a ＂contract＂?\nThey can't mean to be coming for the\ndocument, can they?
It's locked up nice and safe.\nNo one should know where it is...
Phew... What waste of time.\nThe contract is right here!\nHmph! Phantom thief, my silken purse!
Thanks for leading me here, friend.
What?! I say, who goes there?!
Ack! Why is there such a breeze\nin this room?! AGH!
Your Treasure is mine, just like I promised!
Based on what I heard, the current lord\nwasn't supposed to be their lord at all.
Yeah. The guy's got an older brother,\nwhich means HE should be in charge,\nnot this loser.
But after their father, the previous lord,\ngot sick and died, this guy just started\nstruttin' around like he owned the joint.
Does that kind of thing usually work here?\nBecause it seems pretty unlikely.
Yeah, no. Everybody opposed the guy.\nTrouble was, he joined forces with the\nDyrenell Empire.
Wait, but you said this town is already\nunder Empire control.
Yeah, that part kinda bamboozled me.\nBut I asked around, and it sounds like the\nold lord was a real smooth operator.

While the town submitted to the Empire
on paper, he was doing everything he
could to keep it from falling under their
control completely.

The older brother wanted to continue that
policy, but the current lord apparently
went to the Empire and claimed his bro
was some kind of insurrectionist.
So he let the Empire take control in full\nin exchange for a seat at the table.

Yep—and the guy didn't waste a second
once he was officially installed, either.
Jumped right into the good life with both
feet and never looked back.
Well, this is all bad news. In terms of our\nJail heist, it'd be much better if the lord\nand town didn't have any imperial links.

In that case, hold onto your kitty litter,
'cause I ALSO heard that things between
the lord and the Empire ain't exactly
puppies and lollipops right now.
He's been working the Empire guys here\nto the bone, and they can't wait to leave!
Not sure. Apparently the lord has\nsome kind of contract?
Word is, he flashed it at the Empire guys\nand said they were his to command so\nlong as he had it.
Sounds like that contract is the one thing\npreventing the lord from being run out\nof town.
Sure sounds like it. Thing is, not even his\nservants know where he keeps the thing.
Now that's interesting. Finding and taking\nhidden treasures is a phantom thief's\nM.O., you see.
I've been itching to put my skills to use,\nand now it's finally time to go to work!
Your treasure is mine, just like I promised!
Give that contract back, you...you THIEF!\nIt is not for lowborn scum like you to lay\nhands upon!
Yeah, I imagine it would be the end of\nyour little Empire romance if you lost it.
Without the Empire's backing, you're just\nsome jerk in a fancy outfit. Which means\nyou're finished!

Did the sad people of this miserable little
town put you up to this? Well, it matters
not; no matter how they cry and wheedle,
I will ever remain their rightful lord!

It is a serious crime to sneak into the
lord's manor and steal his possessions!
Never mind theft—this is full-fledged
sedition against the Empire itself!

It will be the gallows for you, my friend!
...Ah, but if you do as I command now,
I will ensure that you are treated fairly
and keep your life. So what say you?
Yes, yes, you've realized how meaningless\nyour actions have been. Now hand that\ndocument back to me and—
No, that's not what I'm talking about.\nWho do you think you are, preaching\nabout laws to a phantom thief?
I've only got one thing to say to you:
Stop! Give it back! Don't think for one\nsecond that you will get away with this!
I am the lord of this region! I have the\nEmpire's approval and the Church's seal,\nand so wrought this contract!
You might wanna try that line on someone\nother than a phantom thief, friend.
